<subSubSection id="4A0F56C7ECFB3590641DC9D71533C135" pageId="0" pageNumber="979" type="distribution">
<paragraph id="601C9209095AF4B18FAE51DC43E87EEF" pageId="0" pageNumber="979">Distribution</paragraph>
<paragraph id="EA1B9230E58C9902BDAC1670C7FE6676" pageId="0" pageNumber="979">
This species is thought to be widely distributed in the Holarctic Region. However, 
<bibRefCitation id="21A52699E9473D41EFD5E27B49FA7567" author="Wilson, C. J." journalOrPublisher="Proceedings of the Russian Entomological Society" pageId="0" pageNumber="979" pagination="28 - 33" title="A chromosomal analysis of eight species of Aphodius Illiger, subgenera Agiolinus Schmidt, Agrilinus Mulsant &amp; Rey and Planolinus Mulsant &amp; Rey (Coleoptera: Aphodiidae)" volume="77" year="2006">Wilson and Angus (2006)</bibRefCitation>
demonstrated that the nominative subspecies, 
<taxonomicName id="4DCEF4EF6E18979BF70D68E82D97A165" class="Insecta" family="Aphodiidae" genus="Aphodius" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Aphodius vittatus" order="Coleoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="979" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subspecies" species="vittatus" subspecies="vittatus">Aphodius vittatus vittatus</taxonomicName>
Say, 1825, occurring in North America, has a karyotype different from that of Palearctic subspecies 
<taxonomicName id="526041A6F03FD4FE40ADCB1E4D6E6DEC" class="Insecta" family="Aphodiidae" genus="Aphodius" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Aphodius vittatus" order="Coleoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="979" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subspecies" species="vittatus" subspecies="mundus">Aphodius vittatus mundus</taxonomicName>
Reitter, 1892, 
<taxonomicName id="E487329125A55477DE470F23356B5809" class="Insecta" family="Aphodiidae" genus="Aphodius" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Aphodius vittatus" order="Coleoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="979" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subspecies" species="vittatus" subspecies="sellatus">Aphodius vittatus sellatus</taxonomicName>
Mannerheim, 1852, and 
<taxonomicName id="7FBCE3D2598EC7B881C61647DBB3128F" class="Insecta" family="Aphodiidae" genus="Aphodius" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Aphodius vittatus" order="Coleoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="979" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subspecies" species="vittatus" subspecies="tjanshanicus">Aphodius vittatus tjanshanicus</taxonomicName>
Balthasar, 1956. Therefore, 
<taxonomicName id="0972A5445F8ACC9D94F6F9BD03225B29" class="Insecta" family="Aphodiidae" genus="Aphodius" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Aphodius vittatus" order="Coleoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="979" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="vittatus">Aphodius vittatus</taxonomicName>
can be a complex of closely related species. In the Lower Volga region, 
<taxonomicName id="5B937AE7A68A8FB42B1F2A8BDDA2C73F" class="Insecta" family="Aphodiidae" genus="Aphodius" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Aphodius vittatus" order="Coleoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="979" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subspecies" species="vittatus" subspecies="mundus">Aphodius vittatus mundus</taxonomicName>
occurs.
</paragraph>
